ACTIVATE VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT
(base) nitin@nitin-Latitude-3490:~/PythonWS/task1$ source venv/bin/activate
AFTER ACTIVATION
(venv) (base) nitin@nitin-Latitude-3490:~/PythonWS/task1$ python server1.py


INSTALLING OLDER VERSION OF PYTHON
https://help.dreamhost.com/hc/en-us/articles/215489338-Installing-and-using-virtualenv-with-Python-2
1. wget http://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.7.15/Python-2.7.15.tgz
2. tar zxvf Python-2.7.15.tgz
3. cd Python-2.7.15
4. ./configure --prefix=$HOME/opt/python-2.7.15 --with-ensurepip=install
5. make
6. make install
7. CREATE VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT
virtualenv -p /home/username/opt/python-2.7.15/bin/python my_project
IF BELOW ERROR COMES --
import zlib
ImportError: No module named zlib
INSTALL THE LIBRARY --
sudo apt-get install zlib1g-dev
REPEAT STEPS (6,7)

AUTHENTICATING REST API IN PYTHON FLASK
1. HTTP basic authentication
-- Based on username, password
-- Server stores username and password (possibly db)
-- client sends username, password along with request
-- Server authenticates the user with username and password
--- If it is correct, then the client is provided with result
-- Library used --> pip install Flask-HTTPAuth
-- Link --> http://polyglot.ninja/securing-rest-apis-basic-http-authentication-python-flask/



